# GitHub Actions

## Manual workflow (`gh`)

Full copy-paste steps: [`docs/usage.md`](../docs/usage.md).

## Workflows

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `mirror-poll.yml` | Push/cron (~hourly)/manual: runs `yarn mirror-poll` (dispatch when HEAD != upstream) |
| `config/mirror-template/mirror-merge.yml` (installed as `.github/workflows/mirror-merge.yml` on branch `msys2-apiss-mirror-merge`) | `repository_dispatch`, manual (`clean=true`) |

Dry-run manifest verification: run locally (`yarn mirror-merge --dry-run --skip-fetch`); see
[`docs/run-local.md`](../docs/run-local.md).

## Mirror repos (separate repositories)

| Mirror | Upstream | Replay into msys2-apiss |
|--------|----------|-------------------------|
| `msys2-apiss/MSYS2-packages` | `msys2/MSYS2-packages` | yes (`ports/`) |
| `msys2-apiss/MINGW-packages` | `msys2/MINGW-packages` | yes (`ports-mingw/`) |
| `msys2-apiss/mingw-w64` | [SourceForge mingw-w64](https://git.code.sf.net/p/mingw-w64/mingw-w64) | no (mirror-only) |
| `msys2-apiss/glibc` | [sourceware glibc](https://sourceware.org/git/glibc.git) | no (mirror-only) |

Branch layout: **`msys2-apiss-sync`** holds workflow and config; **`master`** is a pure
fast-forward copy of upstream (no workflow commits on master).

Template: `config/mirror-template/mirror-sync.yml`. Per-repo JSON:
`config/mirror-sync/<repo-name>.json` (applied to `sync/.github/mirror-sync.json`
by `yarn fetch-mirrors`).

## Runner

- Prefer `ubuntu-latest` with `actions/setup-node@v4` and Node.js 26+.
- Run `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` before running sync commands.
- `mirror-poll.yml` and local mirror commands use **`gh`** (`gh auth login`
  locally). CI sets `GH_TOKEN` from `secrets.SYNC_DISPATCH_TOKEN` (fallback
  `github.token`; see [`usage.md`](../docs/usage.md)).

## Concurrency

```yaml
concurrency:
  group: mirror-merge
  cancel-in-progress: false
```

Long sync runs must not be cancelled by the next hourly cron. Scheduled runs
skip when another `mirror-merge` job is already in progress; dispatch and
manual runs queue until the current run finishes.

## Dispatch events

Two names appear in logs and config; they target different blocks and mechanisms:

| Name | From | To | Mechanism |
|------|------|-----|-----------|
| `workflow_dispatch_mirror_sync` | Block 2 (`mirror-poll`) | Block 3 (`mirror-sync.yml` on mirror repo) | GitHub Actions **workflow_dispatch** API on ref `msys2-apiss-mirror-sync` |
| `workflow_dispatch_mirror_merge` | Block 3 (`mirror-sync` notify) | Block 4 (`mirror-merge.yml` on destination) | **repository_dispatch** event-type (package mirrors with `Notify.Enabled`) |

Block 2 never sends `repository_dispatch`. Block 3 notify never uses
`workflow_dispatch_mirror_sync`. Manual Block 4 runs use `workflow_dispatch` on
`mirror-merge.yml` (`gh workflow run ...`).

## Secrets

Set with `gh secret set`; not used by local tooling (`gh auth login` instead).

- `SYNC_DISPATCH_TOKEN`: same PAT on **`msys2-apiss/msys2-apiss-sync`** (Block 2
  [`mirror-poll.yml`](../.github/workflows/mirror-poll.yml) `GH_TOKEN`) and on
  package mirrors **`MSYS2-packages`**, **`MINGW-packages`** (Block 3
  `repository_dispatch` to Block 4 when `Notify.Enabled` is true).
- `MIRROR_PUSH_SSH_KEY`: mirrors with `PushViaSsh` true (e.g. gcc); deploy key
  for `git@github.com` push.
- Mirror-only repos with `Notify.Enabled` false use `github.token` inside
  mirror-sync when `SYNC_DISPATCH_TOKEN` is unset on that mirror repo.

## Push policy

- Push destination branches `upstream`, `upstream-ports`, and
  `upstream-ports-mingw`.
- Track cursors in destination branches, not a committed sync state file.
- Skip destination push when script reports no new commits.
- Use bot identity: `github-actions[bot]`.

## Permissions

```yaml
permissions:
  contents: read   # this repo
```

CI clone/push to `msys2-apiss/msys2-apiss` uses `gh` with `GH_TOKEN`:
`${{ github.token }}`.
